column17: The incident occurred along O'Connor street.
column18: 09/20/1972: A letter bomb addressed to an official was discovered and defused at the Israeli Embassy along O'Connor Street in Ottawa, Canada. This was one of 74 letter bombs that were mailed from Amsterdam and were discovered or detonated between September 19, 1972 and September 28, 1972. Black September claimed responsibility for the incidents.
column127: \\"\"26 more bombs sent to Israelis here"
